## Quick Reference

### Installation (3 Methods)

#### Method 1: Supabase Dashboard (Easiest)
1. Open SQL Editor in Supabase Dashboard
2. Copy/paste migration SQL > Run
3. Copy/paste seed SQL > Run
4. Done!

#### Method 2: Supabase CLI (Best for Teams)
```bash
supabase link --project-ref YOUR_REF
supabase db push
supabase db seed
```

### Quick Validation

```sql
SELECT 
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM organizations) as orgs,      -- 1
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users) as users,             -- 11
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM tracks) as tracks,           -- 7
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM playlists) as playlists,     -- 3
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM assignments) as assignments; -- 3
```

## Database Schema

### Tracks table - Article body in `transcript`
- **Article-type tracks:** Body content is stored in the **`transcript`** column (not only `content_text`). For previews, KB viewer, and publish validation, use **`transcript` first, then `content_text`** (e.g. `transcript || content_text || article_body`). For `type === 'article'`, treat `transcript` as the primary body field.

### Entity Relationship Overview

```
Organization (root)
  |
  |--- Districts
  |     |--- Stores
  |           |--- Users (employees)
  |
  |--- Roles
  |     |--- Users
  |
  |--- Tracks (content)
  |     |--- User Progress
  |     |--- Album Tracks
  |
  |--- Albums
  |     |--- Album Tracks (> Tracks)
  |     |--- Playlist Albums
  |
  |--- Playlists
  |     |--- Assignments (> Users)
  |     |--- Playlist Albums (> Albums)
  |     |--- Playlist Tracks (> Tracks)
  |
  |--- Assignments
  |     |--- User Progress (> Tracks)
  |
  |--- Certifications (templates)
  |     |--- User Certifications (issued)
  |
  |--- Forms (templates)
  |     |--- Form Blocks (fields)
  |     |--- Form Submissions (responses)
  |
  |--- KB Categories
  |     |--- KB Articles
  |           |--- KB Attachments
  |
  |--- Notifications (> Users)
  |
  |--- Activity Logs (audit trail)
```

## Security

### Multi-Tenant Isolation

Every table has `organization_id` with RLS policies ensuring users only see their own organization's data.

### Role-Based Access

- **Admins:** Full access to organization data
- **Managers:** Team/store data access
- **Employees:** Personal data only
